text: The observed prevalence of H5N1-positive market days varied between rounds (median: 12.35; range: 6.8-19.5%) although this difference was not significant (χ 2 p-value = 0.48) ( Table 3) . The observed prevalence of H5N6-positive market days increased significantly (χ 2 p < 0.001) over Rounds 4-6 from 0.7 to 26% ( Table 3) .
